    "id": "1776746208029",
    "text": "I have reviewed the current and previous conversations to distill the master list of features, fixes, and \"God Build\" requirements for SocialHoardr. This consolidated list covers the UI stabilization, core hoarding logic, and the \"Nexus Intelligence\" layer.\n\n### 🏛️ The \"God Build\" Master Roadmap\n\n#### 1. UI/UX & Aesthetics (The Pixel-Perfect Layer)\n*   **Aesthetic Standard**: High-fidelity glassmorphism, dark-mode optimization, and premium typography (Inter/Roboto).\n*   **YouTube Topbar (The \"6 Things\")**:\n    *   A pill-shaped, translucent control group injected into the YouTube masthead (to the left of the \"Create\" button).\n    *   **The Icons**: Signal (AI Sort), Notifications (Hoardr Inbox), Statistics (Overlay Toggle), Catch Up (Rocket), Vault (Archive), and Trash (Clear Session).\n*   **Nexus Floater**:\n    *   **Normal Click (YouTube)**: Toggles the \"old\" in-page statistics overlay (no popups).\n    *   **Normal Click (Other Sites)**: Opens the SocialHoardr Vault.\n    *   **Modifier Click (Opt/Alt)**: Opens the advanced \"Nexus Menu\" for global orchestration.\n*   **Notification Panel**: Floating, glassmorphic inbox with smooth scrolling and high contrast for unread alerts.\n\n#### 2. YouTube Stabilization (Content & Analytics)\n*   **Smart Hoarding**: Automated capture of video duration, channel names, and timestamps (fixing previous duration parsing inaccuracies).\n*   **One-Click Transcripts**: Command to auto-open the YouTube transcript panel, extract text, and save it to the Vault with a high-fidelity visual preview.\n*   **Signal Mode**: A persistent state that filters recommendations based on \"Learning\" vs. \"Distraction\" metadata (Nexus Intelligence).\n*   **Ad-Dodge Analytics**: Tracking and visualizing total ads avoided and time saved.\n\n#### 3. Nexus Intelligence & Vault\n*   **Hoarding Density**: A 90-day pulse heatmap in the Vault visualizing activity across all platforms (X, IG, Reddit, YT).\n*   **Signal Intelligence (Audit)**: AI-driven categorization of hoarded content to audit attention patterns (identifying momentum-heavy content vs. filler).\n*   **Unified Search**: Global search across all captured texts, transcripts, and notifications with platform and date filters.\n*   **Data Export**: Filter-respecting CSV/JSON exports that actually match the visible UI view (fixing the \"exporting everything\" bug).\n\n#### 4. Cross-Platform Coverage\n*   **X (Twitter)**: Stealth hoarding of tweets, including \"Suggested\" content tracking and spam detection.\n*   **Instagram**: Capturing Reels, Highlights, and Profile state.\n*   **Twitch/Reddit**: Live sighting capture and subreddit density tracking.\n*   **Gmail**: Review mode to summarize inbox state.\n\n#### 5. Infrastructure & Resilience\n*   **Nexus Webhook**: Real-time automation layer that sends hoarded signals to your global hub (Gravity Hub).\n*   **Resilient Injection**: Script stability that survives YouTube's Polymer DOM updates via a multi-selector fallback strategy.\n*   **Clean Messaging**: Simplified communication between `nexus.js` and content scripts using `postMessage` and unified chrome message listeners.\n\n### ⚠️ Current Blockers for the Smarter Model:\n*   **Syntax Normalization**: The IDE occasionally flags valid template literals as JSX or \"Invalid Characters\" due to parser conflicts.\n*   **DOM Injection Overlap**: Managing the z-index and placement when other extensions (like Multiselect) are active.\n*   **Background Lifecycle**: Ensuring the service worker doesn't go dormant during long video hoarding sessions.\n\nThis list represents the complete \"Radical Logic\" you've been working toward—a frictionless, AI-ready memory layer for your browsing sessions.",
